Everyone should see this. Very interesting documentary I must say. But for every answer presented here, there are a 1000 more new questions that need to be addressed. This is hard stuff to digest, although I'm consider myself being more of "a believer" than a sceptical. This is not just about the UFO-phenomenon, but also handles the earth's political and economical systems, our technical and medical progress together with the military, media and religion aspects to the whole universe and the history of mankind. (Did I say it raises more questions than answers ?!) The documentary is of course, as always with these subjects US focused, but several of the interviewed people /witnesses are not the usual well-known (or infamous) UFO-researchers, but seemingly sane and trustworthy scientists, pilots etc which make the stated truths more "disturbing" and harder to make excuses for. You won't  see any cults, lunatics or freaks in this one. Most frequent quote is "The evidence is overwhelming", and I have to agree. The documentary left me with an incredibly strong I want to know more about all of it feeling. Knowledge is power.
I guess I have to give this one a chance. Thanks for the upload.

Well. 

There may be UFO's, there may not be. 
I'd say this docu proves little, if anything. 

associating to the Adamski fund and the works by George Adamski himself (died 1965) severely diminishes the credability of the program. 

Adamski thought he had met a ETI from Venus, and at one point claimed that he had been invited to a conference on saturn. (see wikipedia)

Logically speaking, the chances that we are not alone in a potentially endless universe is huge. 
This however does not mean that we have been visited by ETI*S. 

Given our ol' faithfull E=mc2 + the fact that space appears to be flat, not convulsed, makes intergalactic spaceflight very unlikely and timeconsuming, no matter level of technology. 

refering to the web for giving the term "fastwalker" veracity is not convincing either, the hits you get is from a)SafeSpace's own site B)sites like YouTube etc and other belivers. 

Gimme some classified documents goddammit! 

The ZetaRetuli reference is not very convincing either.. Binary starsystems is not very promising for development of life. First of, the stars rotation round eachother causes gravitational shifts that could be harfmul. Second, this may also result in very shifting temperatures. Third, binary systems is less likely to host planets, due to the fact that the stars will need most of the matter available. 

Also, one of the stars in Zeta Retuli appears to be a pulsating star, wich would make the temperatures in the system would be even more shifting and unhospitable. 

Apart from all this critizism, the docu mostly contains the traditional tales by UFO belivers, including the reoccuring claims that "we have classified documents". However, we get no "footnotes" or other ways to verify the claims.
